README
===
This website helps Android developers get the best audio performance from their apps.

It is hosted using Github Pages [https://pages.github.com/] and uses the Jekyll site generator to convert markdown content into static html.

Making changes
===
Before you start you'll need to set up Jekyll locally to view any changes you make. Instructions: https://help.github.com/articles/using-jekyll-with-pages/

Now clone this repo (or your fork of it):

git clone https://github.com/googlesamples/android-audio-high-performance

Now switch to the gh-pages branch:

git checkout -b gh-pages origin/gh-pages

Test your changes locally using the Jekyll server. To start it do:

bundle exec jekyll serve

Now open your web browser at
http://localhost:4000/android-audio-high-performance/
